**Concert Reservation Component**
=====================================

**Overview**
---------------

The `ConcertReservation` component is a crucial part of the online reservation system for concerts in a Blazor Server application. It effectively manages the available capacity of each concert, ensuring real-time updates for connected clients. This component is designed to be user-friendly, accessible, and responsive across various devices.

**Template Format**
-------------------

```html
<!-- ConcertReservation.razor -->
<template>
    <div class="concert-reservation-container">
        <h2>Concert Reservations</h2>
        <div class="concerts-container">
            @foreach (var concert in Concerts)
            {
                <ConcertReservationItem concert="@concert" />
            }
        </div>
    </div>
</template>

@code {
    // Collection of Concert objects
    private List<Concert> Concerts { get; set; } = new List<Concert>();

    // Method to add a new Concert object
    public void AddConcert(Concert concert)
    {
        Concerts.Add(concert);
        StateHasChanged();
    }

    // Method to update the available capacity of a Concert object
    public void UpdateCapacity(int concertId, int newCapacity)
    {
        var concert = Concerts.FirstOrDefault(c => c.Id == concertId);
        if (concert != null)
        {
            concert.AvailableCapacity = newCapacity;
            StateHasChanged();
        }
    }
}
```

**ConcertReservationItem Component**
--------------------------------------

```html
<!-- ConcertReservationItem.razor -->
<template>
    <div class="concert-item">
        <h3>@Concert.Name</h3>
        <p>Available Capacity: @Concert.AvailableCapacity / @Concert.TotalCapacity</p>
        <button @onclick="() => UpdateCapacity()">Update Capacity</button>
    </div>
</template>

@code {
    // Concert object
    private Concert Concert { get; set; }

    // Method to update the available capacity of the Concert object
    private async Task UpdateCapacity()
    {
        // Simulate an update request to the server
        await Http.SendAsync(new HttpRequestMessage(HttpMethod.Post, $"updateCapacity/{Concert.Id}"));
    }
}
```

**Concert Class**
-----------------

```csharp
// Concert.cs
public class Concert
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public int TotalCapacity { get; set; }
    public int AvailableCapacity { get; set; }
}
```

**Interaction and Functionality**
----------------------------------

1.  The `ConcertReservation` component fetches a list of `Concert` objects from the server and displays each concert's available capacity.
2.  When a user clicks the "Update Capacity" button, the `ConcertReservationItem` component sends a request to the server to update the available capacity of the corresponding concert.
3.  The server updates the available capacity and notifies all connected clients through a real-time update mechanism (e.g., SignalR).
4.  Upon receiving the update, the client-side `ConcertReservation` component updates the available capacity of the affected concert, ensuring that all connected clients have the latest information.

**Accessibility and Responsiveness**
---------------------------------------

1.  The component uses semantic HTML structure for better accessibility.
2.  The layout is responsive and adapts to various screen sizes and devices.
3.  The component utilizes ARIA attributes to provide a better experience for screen readers and other assistive technologies.

**Example Use Cases**
------------------------

1.  A user navigates to the concert reservation page and sees the available capacity for each concert.
2.  The user updates the available capacity of a concert by clicking the "Update Capacity" button.
3.  The server receives the update request and notifies all connected clients, who then update their local available capacity values.

**Code Quality and Readability**
-------------------------------

1.  The code adheres to standard coding conventions and guidelines.
2.  Variable and method names are clear and descriptive.
3.  Comments are provided to explain complex logic and functionality.

By following this design and implementing the necessary features, the `ConcertReservation` component will provide an efficient and user-friendly experience for managing concert reservations in a real-time online system.

